products.title: Pastrami Sandwich Bar Party Box
products.description:
Steps for a classic pastrami sandwich:
1. Grill your bread: Butter both sides of the bread. On a hot skillet, place bread to grill. When browned, flip to the other side. Remove when both sides of the bread are golden.
2. Spread the mustard on both pieces of bread.
3. Layer the pastrami. Go as high as you want! We don’t consider it a sandwich unless you need both hands to hold it.
4. Optional: Layer sauerkraut on top of the pastrami. Our sauerkraut isn’t very “sauer” so don’t be worried about too much acidity. It adds a nice crunch and JUST the right amount of acid.
5. Close the sandwich. Cut it in half if you’re intimidated. Chow down. Eat a pickle.

To reheat the meat - just microwave for a few seconds. Be careful not to over nuke or else it will dry up.

products.title: Reuben Sandwich Bar Party Box
products.description:
Steps for a classic Reuben sandwich:
1. Grill your bread: Butter both sides of the bread. On a hot skillet, place bread to grill. When browned, flip to the other side. Remove when both sides of the bread are golden.
2. Be lavish! Spread the Russian dressing generously on both pieces of bread.
3. Layer the corned beef. Go as high as you want! We don’t consider it a sandwich unless you need both hands to hold it.
4. Layer sauerkraut on top of the corned beef. Our sauerkraut isn’t very “sauer” so don’t be worried about too much acidity. It adds a nice crunch and JUST the right amount of acid.
5. Melty cheese tastes the best, so just nuke the cheese for 15 seconds or until soft, then pour it over the sauerkraut.
6. Sprinkle paprika over the cheese. This adds that extra “oomph”.
7. Close the sandwich. Cut it in half if you’re intimidated. Chow down. Eat a pickle.

To reheat the meat - just microwave for a few seconds. Be careful not to over nuke or else it will dry up.

products.title: Hot Pastrami Sandwich Kit
products.description:
Hot Pastrami Sandwich Kit Instructions:

1. Read the directions all the way to the end so there are no surprises, and practice proper hygiene by washing our hands. Fill your pot with water and boil the water until it reaches a rolling boil. When boiling, place the packet of pastrami in the water for 5-7 minutes. Remove from the water, open the bag and put the hot pastrami on a plate.

2. While the water is boiling, slice the rye bread. You can make 1 huge sandwich or 2 smaller ones. Thickness is up to you. Spread butter on BOTH sides. It helps to soften the butter a bit.

3. Heat your skillet on medium heat. When hot, placed buttered slices of bread on it. Grill until a bit brown, then flip to the other side. Remove from the pan and place on a plate.

4. Spread mustard on the inner part of the bread. Remember to make sure the slices align properly. Layer the pastrami on the bread, as high as you want it to go. Close the sandwich. If you want, hold it firmly and slice it down the middle.
products.short_description:
Hot Pastrami Kit by Fearless Apron. An easy kit to make your own. It comes with pastrami, rye bread, mustard, butter, and dill pickles.

Good for 2, with vaccuum-packed pastrami. Heat and assemble your own sandwich so it has that freshly-made goodness. Can stay 3 days in the fridge, unopened.
